This PlantUML diagram represents the **Team Planning App LLD**, structured into 7 packages representing 7 modules of the application. Each module has its own classes containing attributes and operations, and classes in lower-level packages rely on classes in higher-level packages. The relationships are represented using standard PlantUML relationship types (--> and ..>) to indicate dependencies.

The diagram includes 5 notes with the stereotype <<api>> to highlight the API-related logic and to attach API notes to API-related classes. The overall structure and names follow the **Team Planning App LLD** and the rules provided.

To keep the diagram simple and follow the rules, no interfaces, enums, abstract classes, or other advanced features have been used, and only the standard PlantUML syntax has been employed.
